	<tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/Arcticspectre?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">Arcticspectre</a>&nbsp;<a href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23stars"><img align=absmiddle src=/images/star2.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="333 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr class="BoardRowA"><td nowrap="false" class="BoardRowA"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/collection/Arcticspectre"><font size="1">collection (0)</font></a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/wishlist/Arcticspectre"><font size="1">wishlist (0)</font></a></td></tr></table><!-- /WISH & COLL STUFF	--><span style="font-weight: bold;">Title:</span> Lost in the Shiverpeaks <br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 333<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Oct 04<br></span><br></td><td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span>&nbsp;11/19/04 7:08am&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> replace/rework soul reaping?</td></tr><tr valign=top><td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">I've posted in other threads before about this issue, but I thought I'd give it it's own thread as it's a topic in it's own right. Anyway, on to the issue... <br>  <br> Soul Reaping seems to be lacking as a primary attribute. Why? Because it's only useful in specific strategies and in specific situations, but for the most part it is pretty useless. Given, in these situations it is a decent attribute, but in all others it is next to useless. <br>  <br> ---Useful strategy: Death magic summons. When your summons die you gain mana. A great attribute for a summoner. <br>  <br> ---Useful situation: Battles with many enemies. When there are a lot of enemies(especially weak ones) in one huge battle where you have no time to recooperate between kills it it great. <br>  <br> In most every other way soul reaping is terrible: <br>  <br> If you are fighting a boss? Weak. Where are the multiple bodies to drop? <br>  <br> If you are using blood magic/curses? Weak. You don't have summons to die, so very little use of soul reaping. <br>  <br> If you are using death magic but manage to keep your summons alive? Weak. <br>  <br> If you are using a ranged build such as N/R, N/E, N/Mo or N/Me? Weak. If you aren't close enough to the action you wont get any mana even when something does die. <br>  <br> If you are going through an explorable area/mission with gaps of time between battles? Weak. You have enough time to regen the mana between battles anyway. (This is a large part of GW) <br>  <br> Most of the other classes have a primary attribute that is MUCH more useful in many more situations. The ranger and monk could be contested, but to a much lesser degree than the necromancer. The warrior, mesmer, and elementalist all have very useful primary attributes that are useful in most every situation. <br>  <br> Suggestion: <br>  <br>  **IDEA** <br>  <br> What if each death gives you an extra arrow of energy regen for _____ duration where _____ is related to how many points you have in soul reaping. Soul reaping could give you a max of 3 extra arrows(from 3 seperate deaths), thus you can leave battle, your energy regens super fast as normal after battle, but into the next battle you might still have extra the energy regen if your soul reaping is high enough. <br>  <br> Just to toss some numbers around... 1 points in soul reaping could give each kill's arrow 10 seconds and each extra point in soul reaping gives 5 extra seconds...so at 12 youll have 65 seconds per arrow. A bit much? Maybe, but you have to consider you're investing a lot of your points into an attribute with no skills tied to it. <br>  <br> Soul Reaping: Each death nearby gives one extra arrow of energy regeneration for 10..65 seconds(1-12 points) Soul reaping may only give a maximum of 3 arrows of extra regeneration at any one time. <br>  <br> I'm not standing by the numbers, but the concept I think is pretty good. <br> <p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/post.asp?brd=22827&topic=78998889">Post Reply</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=78998889" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=976509">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=976509">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/JerekPr?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">JerekPr</a>&nbsp;<a href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23stars"><img align=absmiddle src=/images/star2.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="260 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr class="BoardRowA"><td nowrap="false" class="BoardRowA"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/collection/JerekPr"><font size="1">collection (0)</font></a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/wishlist/JerekPr"><font size="1">wishlist (0)</font></a></td></tr></table><!-- /WISH & COLL STUFF	--><span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 260<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Nov 04<br></span><br></td><td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span>&nbsp;11/19/04 7:20am&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> RE: replace/rework soul reaping?</td></tr><tr valign=top><td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">I think you should concretely and thoroughly test it out next BPE and see if your opinion is still the same. I know people who have been very successful with it. <br> <p></p><span cl